narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Definitely take it! I only hope that future sections are as small as ours, since I think having a 9 person class made it very easy for Professor SP to give us targeted and complete individual feedback.
I have never liked an English class, I loved this one. You're reading constantly but everything is connected and very interesting.

It is a neat way to look at ethical topics in medicine while reading good literature. For an English major the discussion was a bit low level because the class was small and made up mostly of pre-meds, but the readings were interesting and the workload was not too bad.

This is a great course if you like thinking about some heavy, dark issues in medical ethics. It is also a good course if you like literary analysis, or if you are thinking about writing about healthcare and medicine with an ethical bent.
